They give a false sense of a fulfilling life.
But we can look at the upper class of society. Money is of no concern. They can buy and do freely as the please. They can jetset around the world and be happy It is a waste of money.

We may pay more to buy a larger home for our family. These may be material objects but they bring us sense of satisfaction and happiness. My grandparents' health was ailing. They could no longer live alone. My father and I saved to buy a larger home. One could scoff it was too large, too decadent. We sacrificed our time and effort to buy a larger home so my grandparents could live with us, we could take care of them, and we could all cohabitate together comfortably. This new \"toy\", our home, brought us a sense of happiness and peace knowing we could provide and take care of our family.
